President Muhammadu Buhari on Sunday extended heartfelt condolences to the former First Lady of Nigeria, Marayam Abacha, and the Abacha family on the death of their son, Abdullahi. The Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity to the President, Garba Shehu, in a statement on Sunday, indicated that the “President’s prayers and thoughts are with the family of Abacha as they grieve the passing of the young Abdullahi. “The President prays for the repose of the soul of the deceased and comfort for those who mourn.” 